Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editRotate(25.10)                                            editRotate(25.10)

Name
       editRotate - Flips or rotates selected wires and vias

Syntax
       editRotate

       [-help]

       [-mode {group | single}]

       [-rotate_point {<x y>}]

       {-flip {MX MY} | -rotate {R90 R180 R270}}

       Flips  or  rotates  selected  wires and vias. Use this command for more
       flexible custom routing and fixing DRC violations using existing wires.
       Using the editRotate command, you can:

              * Flip selected wires or vias on the X or Y axis (MX or MY)

              * Rotate the selected wires or vias by 90, 180, or  270  degrees
                (R90, R180, or R270).

       The selected object is rotated or flipped based on current orientation,
       and  the  lower-left  coordinate of the wire/via remains the same after
       rotation or flip.

       You can also flip or rotate  multiple  objects  simultaneously  as  one
       group.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  the  usage of the command. For a detailed description of
              the command, use the man command:

              man editRotate

       -flip {MX MY}
              Flips a wire or via. If you specify MX, the selected  object  is
              flipped  on the X axis. If you specify MY, the object is flipped
              on the Y axis.

       -mode {group single}
              Rotates multiple selected wires and vias at the same time  using
              the specified mode:

              * group - Flips or rotates the selected objects as a group. This
                is the default mode when multiple objects are selected.

                In this mode, the tool flips or rotates the bounding box which
                encloses all the selected objects.

              * single - Flips or rotates the selected objects individually.

       -rotate {R90 R180 R270}
              Rotates wires or vias by 90, 180, or 270 degrees, as specified.

       -rotate_point {x y}
              Specifies  the point around which the wire should be rotated. If
              this option is not specified, the selected  wires/vias  are  ro-
              tated   around   the   lower-left  corner  of  bounding  box  of
              wires/vias.

Examples
              * The following command rotates the selected wire by 90 degrees:

                editRotate -rotate R90

              * The following command rotates the selected object, which orig-
                inally has R90 as its original orientation by 90 degrees:

                editRotate -rotate R90

                The final orientation of the object will be R180 as shown  be-
                low:

              * The following command rotates the bounding box of the selected
                wires by 90 degrees to rotate the wires as one group:

                editRotate -rotate R90 -mode group

              * The  following command rotates the selected wires individually
                by 90 degrees:

                editRotate -rotate R90 -mode single

              *

                The following commands rotate the selected wire by 90 and  180
                degrees,  respectively, around the specified rotation point, x
                y:

                editRotate -rotate R90 -rotate_point x y

                editRotate -rotate R180 -rotate_point x y

              *

                The following commands rotate the selected group of  wires  by
                90  and  180 degrees, respectively, around the specified rota-
                tion point, x y:

                editRotate -rotate R90 -mode group -rotate_point x y

                editRotate -rotate R180 -mode group -rotate_point x y

